Key Match Events: Corbin Carroll hit a go-ahead grand slam in the eighth inning to secure an 8-5 victory for the D-backs over the Mets.
Carroll hit two home runs in the game, contributing significantly to the D-backs' win.
Eduardo Rodriguez had a strong start, not allowing a baserunner through the first four innings.
The Mets rallied to take a 5-4 lead in the fifth and sixth innings before the D-backs' comeback.
Post-Match Reflections: Corbin Carroll expressed that he is not trying to be the team's hero but aims to help the team win every day.
D-backs manager Torey Lovullo acknowledged the frustration in the dugout during the middle innings.
Mets center fielder Brandon Nimmo praised Carroll's performance and acknowledged his significant contribution to the D-backs' comeback.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The D-backs have been performing exceptionally well, with 21 wins and a +64 run differential since July 29, leading all of baseball.
The D-backs' 35-14 record since July 1 is the best in the Majors in that span.
